<p class="p1"><span class="s7">Nicholas Sims-Williams, Frantz Grenet, and Aleksandr Podushkin, &ldquo;Les plus&nbsp;anciens monuments&nbsp;de&nbsp;la&nbsp;langue sogdienne: Les inscriptions de Kultobe au Kazakhstan,&rdquo; </span><em>Comptes rendus des s&eacute;ances de l&rsquo;Acad&eacute;mie des Inscriptions et Belles-Lettres,</em><span class="s7"> 2007, pp. </span>1005-34.</p>
<p class="p1">Nicholas Sims-Williams and James Hamilton, <em>Documents turco-sogdiens du IX<sup>e</sup> - X<sup>e</sup> si&egrave;cle de Touen-houang,</em> London, 1990. English tr. as <em>Turco-Sogdian Documents from 9th-10th Century Dunuang,</em> Corpus Inscriptionum Iranicarum Part II, Vol. III/IV, London, 2015.</p>
<p class="p1">Nicholas Sims-Williams and Bi Bo, &ldquo;Sogdian Documents from Khotan, I: Four Economic Documents,&rdquo; <em>JAOS</em> 130/4, 2011, pp. 497-508.</p>
<p class="p1">Idea, &ldquo;Sogdian Documents from Khotan, II: Letters and Miscellaneous Fragments,&rdquo; <em>JAOS</em> 135/2, 2015, pp. 261-282.</p>
<p class="p1">Prods Oktor Skj&aelig;rv&oslash;, &ldquo;Aramaic Scripts for Iranian Languages,&rdquo; in Peter T. Daniels and William Bright, eds., <em>The World&rsquo;s Writing Systems, </em>New York, 1996, pp. 515-35.</p>
<p class="p1">Werner Sundermann, &ldquo;Manichaean Literature in Iranian Languages,&rdquo; in M. Macuch and R. E. Emmerick, eds., <em>A History of Persian Literature</em> XVII. <em>The Literature of Pre-Islamic Iran</em>, London, 2009, pp. 197-265.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, <em>Die Rede der Lebendigen Seele. Ein manich&auml;ischer Hymnenzyklus in mittelpersischer und soghdischer Sprache,</em> BTT XXX, Turnhout, 2012.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;On the Growing Turkicization of the Sogdian Language,&rdquo; in E. A. Csato, L. Johanson, A. Rona-Tas, and B. Utas, eds., <em>Turks and Iranians. Interactions in Language and History,</em> Wiesbaden, 2016, pp. 29-36.</p>
<p class="p1">Dieter Weber, <em>Die Stellung der sog. Inchoativa im Mitteliranischen</em>, doctoral diss., G&ouml;ttingen, 1970.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;Also sprach Mandri (Bemerkingen zur direkten Rede im Sogdischen),&rdquo; <em>Indogermansiche Forschungen</em> 76, 1971, pp. 77-83.</p>
<p class="p1">Antje Wendtland, &ldquo;Zu &lt;h&gt; in Soghdischen,&rdquo; <em>G&ouml;ttinger Beitr&auml;ge zur Sprachwissenschaft</em> 1, 1998, pp. 101-10.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, <em>Die Entwickelung von Demonstrativpronomen zu Artikeln im Sogdischen,</em> Wiesbaden, 2011.</p>
<p class="p1">Ilya Yakubovitch, &ldquo;Mugh 1.I Revisited,&rdquo; <em>Studia Iranica</em> 31/2, 2002, pp. 231-53.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;The Syntactic Evolution of Aramaic ZY in Sogdian,&rdquo; <em>Studia Iranica </em>34/2, 2005, pp. 199-230.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;Marriage Sogdian Style,&rdquo; in Heiner Eichner et al., eds., <em>Iranistik in Europa &mdash; Gestern, Heute, Morgen, </em>Vienna, 2006, pp. 307-44.</p>
<p class="p1">Yutaka Yoshida, &ldquo;On the Sogdian infinitives,&rdquo; <em>Journal of Asian and African Studies</em> 18, 1979, pp. 181-95.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;Kirisutokyou Sogudogono Hougenni tsuite&rdquo; (On the dialectology of Christian Sogdian), <em>Oriento</em> 23/1, 1980, pp. 83-93.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;Karabarugasun Hibunno Dogudogobanni tsuite&rdquo; (On the Sogdian version of the Kara Balgasun inscription), <em>Bulletin of the Society of Western and Southern Asiatic Studies, Kyoto University </em>28, 1988, pp. 24-52.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;Sogudomojide Hyoukisareta Kanjion&rdquo; (Chinese in Sogdian script), <em>The Toho Gakuho</em> 66, 1994, pp. 271-380.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;Sogudogo Zatsuroku IV&rdquo; (Sogdian miscellany IV), <em>Studies on the Inner Asian Languages </em>X, 1995, pp. 67-84 with plate III.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;The Sogdian Version of the New Xi&rsquo;an Inscription,&rdquo; in &Eacute;tienne de la Vaissi&egrave;re and &Eacute;ric Trombert, eds., <em>Les Sogdiens en Chine, Paris</em>, 2005, pp. 57-72.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;Sogudogono Keigoni tsuite&rdquo; (Honorific and polite expressions in Sogdian), in Satoko Shirai and Masahiro Shogaito, eds., <em>Philological Studies on Old Central Asian Manuscripts,</em> Kyoto, 2006, pp. 81-94.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;Sogdian,&rdquo; in Gernot Windfuhr, ed., <em>The Iranian Languages</em>, London, 2009a, pp. 279-335.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;Buddhist Literature in Sogdian,&rdquo; in Maria Macuch and Ronald E. Emmerick, eds., <em>A History of Persian Literature</em> XVII. <em>The Literature of Pre-Islamic Iran</em>, London, 2009b, pp. 288-329.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;Minor Moods in Sogdian,&rdquo; in Kazuhiko Yoshida and Brent Vine, eds., <em>East and West. Papers in Indo-European Studies,</em> Bremen, 2009c, pp. 281-93.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;Turco-Sogdian Features,&rdquo; in Werner Sundermann, Almut Hintze, and Fran&ccedil;ois de Blois, eds., <em>Exegisti monumenta: Festschrift in Honour of Nicholas Sims-Williams,</em> Iranica 17, Wiesbaden, 2009d, pp. 571-86.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;Some New Readings in the Sogdian Version of the Karabalgasun Inscription,&rdquo; in Mehmet &Ouml;lmez et al., eds., <em>From &Ouml;t&uuml;ken to Istanbul. 1290 Years of Turkish </em>(<em>720-2010</em>), Istanbul, 2011, pp. 77-86.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;Sogudojinto Kodaityurukuzoku tono Kankeini kansuru Mittsuno Oboegaki&rdquo; (Three philological notes on the Sogdo-Turkish relationship), <em>Memoirs of the Faculty of Letters, Kyoto University</em> 50, 2011a, pp. 1-41.</p>
<p class="p1">Idem, &ldquo;When did Sogdians begin to write vertically?&rdquo; <em>Tokyo University Linguistic Papers</em> 31 (Festschrift for Prof. Hiroshi Kumamoto), 2013, pp. 375-94.</p>
<p class="p1">Yutaka Yoshida and Takao Moriyasu, &ldquo;Kikushi Koshoukoku Jidai Sogudobun Onnadorei Baibaimonnzyo&rdquo; (A Sogdian sale contract of a female slave from the period of the Gaochang kingdom under the rule of Qu clan), <em>Studies on the Inner Asian languages</em> 4, 1988, pp. 1-50.</p>


					<p>(Yutaka Yoshida)</p>

